--------------------Contents--------------------------------------------

This map have 4 different ways to play:

**Normal mode:** Surf for users medium-hard. With 3 ways

-Noob

-Pro

-Skill

**Shotguns mode:** A small part of the map where CT and T fight against each other.

**Scout mode:** This one counts as two. One team starts with scout and must shoot against the other team that must arrive to their position hiding between walls and throwing flashes and smoke grenades.

When you pass Skill part, you can choose between these 5 minigames, or 5 minutes after map starts.

**Climb:** Climb to the top.

**Free Fall:** Fall avoiding the floor and get to the bottom.

**Knife:** Just a knife fight.

**Skate:** Do skate at jail.

**Jump:** Jump the lasers.

It also have some tricks that I hope you enjoy finding them. The codes are hide around the map, just find them.

There is also a **codebar** to access to the armoury from the noob part. A code bar is a number in binary, that you must change to decimal (There are many websites where you can do the change like http://www.disfrutalasmatematicas.com/numeros/binario-decimal-hexadecimal-conversor.html), BUT YOU SHOULD HAVE IN MIND THAT LOGIC COMPARES MAKE YOU SWAP NUMBERS IN THE OTHER WAY. Ex: 1369 is the code bar, and the password is 9631. With this system there are 8191 different passwords, so anyone can enter if they don't know this ;)

**EDIT-> FORGET TO SAY THAT THERE IS AN ADMIN ROOM TO ACTIVE MINIGAMES ON YOUR SERVER, YOU CAN ONLY ACCESS WITH NOCLIP OR TELEPORT.**

--------------Video-----------------------

Video: [http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1lJ6HZCZyos](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1lJ6HZCZyos "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1lJ6HZCZyos")

On the video you can see the normal mode. And I sow there how to pass all parts except skill one, it's to difficult to record and surf with 30-50 fps because of fraps, when I usually have between 250-300

--------------------------------------------

Thx for watching, and please comment & rate, it's my first map, and yes, it took me like a year to make it.

This map is an update to an earlier version (v4).  It was originally inspired by one of my favorite surf maps, skyscraper, and retains some of that blend of surf and shoot, although this version is a little heavier on the surf.  More ramps, more boosts, and more tricks are available now.  You can land on my name in the sky (and tele from there to an invisible platform or just jump off and surf).  From the orange roof, you should be able to surf/fly directly to anywhere in the map once you get the hang of it.  There's a buy zone, weapons room (no awps/semis in the WR), multiple paths from the spawn (six really), and awps available in the trickier places to get to.

The dilemma is to choose the easy, medium, or hard path. Easy gets a mac10, medium a scout, hard an awp/semi-auto. All paths lead eventually to the weapons room which contains weapons other than awps/semi-autos. There is also a floating buyzone that is somewhat tricky to get to.

- Thanks for downloading surf_digital[g]beta_fixed! 
- This map was originally made by X-Shark. I have merely edited it to eliminate spawnkilling and add other attributes.
- The gameplay of this map has NOT been altered.
- Permission was granted by author X-Shark for the release of this map.
- Many thanks to X-Shark for creating surf_digital[g]beta1.

_________________________________________________

To install this map:

- Steam>steamapps>[username]>counter-strike source>cstrike>maps

- Place the surf_digital[g]beta_fixed.bsp in your MAPS folder...done!

_________________________________________________

The changes I have made:

- Surf at spawn is now split into 2 segments with a wall to prevent spawnkilling.
- Teleport at top is now wider to stop players falling off when they teleport.
- Glass near scouts has been retextured (when compiled it came out very bright).
- Scouts zone now has water to prevent fall damage.
- Boosts added when you spawn in jail to stop people camping the corners.
- Glass at jail is now thinner so all weapons can shoot through it.
- Glass at jail top is now retextured to make it easier to see into jail.
- Glass at jail has been lengthened and retextured to prevent camper spots at shotguns.
- Teleport rooms to shotgun and m4a1 spawns at jail are now brighter.
- Jail retextured.
- Other minor fixes.
_________________________________________________

www.dragonrock.org

- STEAM Friends: Target Practice

Otherwise you may contact the original author, X-Shark who can be found at www.solidsurf.info.

About the map ___________________________________________ This map is a combat map. Both teams start off with only a knife. While walking towards the first ramp, you'll notice that there's a small ledge. This ledge will give you all the speed you need to reach the ramp and the next boost. From then, you can go where-ever you want. This map does not have some sort of guideline for surfers, thus giving it a freestyle flavour. Gaining speed There are different ways of gaining speed. Seeing how the obelisk wasn't an optimal way of gaining good speed, I've added a platform with a four-way push. This should backup the telehop way with the obelisks. Guns This map involves nearly all types of guns. There are m3's, mac10's, scouts, two awp's, tmp's, deagles, ak47's, m4a1's and hegrenades. Prison ___________________________________________ Upon falling and entering jail, you will lose all your weapons and in return receive a knife. You'll notice there's not much to the jail. That's because I think a jail should be boring and not fun at all. After all, you don't go there for your own free will. Players outside of the jail have access to a button that opens the jail door, and a button that smashes every prisoner. Also there is a deagle dispenser and a hegrenade dispenser. There is a way to get out of jail without the button, but I'll leave that up to you to discover. Spawn-kill protection system ___________________________________________ You will not be able to spawnkill the first 15 seconds of each round. Both spawns are completely sealed from intruders and remain sealed during these 15 seconds. Teleporting to each spawn by using the obelisks is also not an option. I guess that's all I have to say. I'd like you to enjoy playing this map! =====note===== Due to some bugs, I have updated the bsp. Redownload the map please, it has now the name 'surf_deificus_final'. Thank you.
